<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,366,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A six-gilled species of 
<taxonomicName box="[587,703,367,392]" class="Myxini" family="Myxinidae" genus="Eptatretus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myxiniformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="123" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[587,703,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">Eptatretus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 3/3 multicusp pattern, 9–10 anterior unicusps, and 7–8 posterior unicusps; posterior tip of dental muscle reaching up to the mid-region of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1073,1089,402,416]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">nd</superScript>
gill pouch; total cusps 44–48; total pores 67–69 (prebranchial 12–13, branchial 6, trunk 39–40, and tail 8–11). Uniformly brown colouration on the dorsal and ventral region when fresh (
<figureCitation box="[617,706,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,849,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-372@3.[151,1435,849,1725]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. (A) Holotype (B) Gill apertures (GA) Eptatretus wadgensis sp. nov., CMFRI DNR.: GC.1.1.1.1, 400mm in TL, fresh specimen (photo: K.R. Aju)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) and dark brown when preserved in formalin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="3" pageNumber="123" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,510,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">Description.</emphasis>
Collected specimens ranged from 
<quantity box="[728,876,511,537]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.54" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.08" pageId="3" pageNumber="123" unit="mm" value="354.0" valueMax="400.0" valueMin="308.0">308–400 mm</quantity>
TL. Morphometrics as percentage TL presented in 
<tableCitation box="[151,234,547,573]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,239,151,175]" captionText="TABLE 1. Counts and proportions of Eptatretus wadgensis sp. nov." pageId="3" pageNumber="123">Table 1</tableCitation>
. Body nearly cylindrical and eel-like with velvety smooth skin which lacks scales. Body slightly deeper than wide near prebranchial, branchial, and trunk regions. Cloaca and tail region strongly compressed with tail margin blunt and irregular. Rostrum short and rounded. Presence of two conspicuous eyespots on either side of head. Nasal papilla absent. Preocular length (3.6–4.6% TL) shorter than branchial length (7.7–10.6% TL). Three pairs of barbels on head with first and second short, slender, approximately equal in size (0.7–0.8% TL) and laterally arranged near nostril. Third pair of barbels slightly longer (0.8–0.9% of TL) and placed near mouth. Six gill pouches corresponding to six gill apertures arranged in straight-line approximately at equal distance. Pharyngocutaneous-duct aperture large in size, confluent with 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[483,496,798,812]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">th</superScript>
gill aperture on left side (
<figureCitation box="[783,871,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,849,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-372@3.[151,1435,849,1725]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. (A) Holotype (B) Gill apertures (GA) Eptatretus wadgensis sp. nov., CMFRI DNR.: GC.1.1.1.1, 400mm in TL, fresh specimen (photo: K.R. Aju)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809924" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6809924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="123" startId="3.[151,250,1748,1772]" targetBox="[151,1435,849,1724]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1748,1808]" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,320,1748,1772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">FIGURE 2. (A)</emphasis>
Holotype 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[429,463,1748,1772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">(B)</emphasis>
Gill apertures (GA) 
<taxonomicName authority="Augustina &amp; Sreeram &amp; Sukumaran &amp; Jose, 2022" authorityName="Augustina &amp; Sreeram &amp; Sukumaran &amp; Jose" authorityYear="2022" box="[679,897,1748,1772]" class="Myxini" family="Myxinidae" genus="Eptatretus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myxiniformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="123" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wadgensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[679,897,1748,1772]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">Eptatretus wadgensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[904,986,1748,1772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[904,986,1748,1772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="123" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, CMFRI DNR.: GC.1.1.1.1, 400mm in TL, fresh specimen (photo: K.R. Aju)
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1854,2024]" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">
Two rows of comb-like teeth with sharp tips slightly curved rearward. Anterior and posterior row of dentition on either side with last teeth slender and smaller in size; outer row consisting of a 3-cusp multicusp and 9–10 unicusps; inner row comprises of a 3-cusp multicusp and 7–8 unicusps; total number of cusps 44–48. Palatine tooth present with triangular shaped broad base (
<figureCitation box="[647,718,1962,1988]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1509,1533]" captionTargetBox="[252,1336,181,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-30@5.[252,1336,181,1485]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dentition of Eptatretus wadgensis sp. nov., holotype CMFRI DNR.: GC.1.1.1.1 (A. Anterior row of teeth B. Posterior row of teeth (left series) and palatine tooth (PL)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809930/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Dental muscles broad, long with posterior tip reaching up to mid-region of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[327,343,1998,2012]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">nd</superScript>
gill pouch (
<figureCitation box="[478,547,1998,2024]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Anatomy of Eptatretus wadgensis sp. nov., Paratypes CMFRI DNR GC.1.1.1.4 Separated ventral aorta between 4th and 5th gill pouch. Branchial region (gill pouches (GP), median ventral aorta (MVA), separated ventral aorta (SVA), efferent branchial duct (EBD), dental muscle (DM), heart (H) and liver (L) (photo: K.R. Aju)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809928" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809928/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="123">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809928" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6809928" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809928/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="124" startId="4.[151,250,1918,1942]" targetBox="[151,1436,181,1895]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1918,2015]" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1918,1942]" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
Anatomy of 
<taxonomicName authority="Augustina &amp; Sreeram &amp; Sukumaran &amp; Jose, 2022" authorityName="Augustina &amp; Sreeram &amp; Sukumaran &amp; Jose" authorityYear="2022" box="[414,633,1919,1943]" class="Myxini" family="Myxinidae" genus="Eptatretus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myxiniformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="124" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wadgensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[414,633,1919,1943]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">Eptatretus wadgensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[640,722,1919,1943]" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[640,722,1919,1943]" pageId="4" pageNumber="124" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, Paratypes CMFRI DNR GC.1.1.1.4 Separated ventral aorta between 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[164,175,1955,1969]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">th</superScript>
and 5 
<superScript attach="left" box="[237,248,1955,1969]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">th</superScript>
gill pouch. Branchial region (gill pouches (GP), median ventral aorta (MVA), separated ventral aorta (SVA), efferent branchial duct (EBD), dental muscle (DM), heart (H) and liver (L) (photo: K.R. Aju)
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809930" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6809930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809930/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="125" startId="5.[151,250,1509,1533]" targetBox="[252,1336,181,1485]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1509,1569]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1509,1533]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
Dentition of 
<taxonomicName authority="Augustina &amp; Sreeram &amp; Sukumaran &amp; Jose, 2022" authorityName="Augustina &amp; Sreeram &amp; Sukumaran &amp; Jose" authorityYear="2022" box="[412,629,1509,1533]" class="Myxini" family="Myxinidae" genus="Eptatretus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myxiniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="125" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wadgensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[412,629,1509,1533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">Eptatretus wadgensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[635,716,1509,1533]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[635,716,1509,1533]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype CMFRI DNR.: GC.1.1.1.1 (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1110,1128,1509,1533]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">A</emphasis>
. Anterior row of teeth 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1361,1378,1509,1533]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">B</emphasis>
. Posterior row of teeth (left series) and palatine tooth (PL).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1615,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">
Slime pores segmentally arranged along a straight line on either side ranging from prebranchial to tail regions. Six branchial slime pores placed posterior to six gill apertures on each side with a minor deviation in straight-line alignment of slime pores occurring downward along branchial region. Ventral aorta bifurcating at 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1260,1273,1687,1701]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">th</superScript>
or between 4 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1424,1437,1687,1701]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">th</superScript>
and 5 
<superScript attach="left" box="[211,224,1723,1737]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">th</superScript>
gill pouch. All six EBDs are arranged in equidistance with 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[892,905,1723,1737]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">th</superScript>
EBD convergent with PCD on left side (
<figureCitation box="[1355,1422,1723,1750]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Anatomy of Eptatretus wadgensis sp. nov., Paratypes CMFRI DNR GC.1.1.1.4 Separated ventral aorta between 4th and 5th gill pouch. Branchial region (gill pouches (GP), median ventral aorta (MVA), separated ventral aorta (SVA), efferent branchial duct (EBD), dental muscle (DM), heart (H) and liver (L) (photo: K.R. Aju)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809928" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809928/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Ventral fin-fold low, beginning from midpoint of trunk region and extending up to cloaca. Caudal fin starts posterior to cloaca and extends around tail.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1615,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">
Colouration: Body uniformly brown on dorsal and ventral regions in fresh specimens. First pair of large barbels dark brown, remaining two pairs of short barbels light brown. Eyespot pale or whitish. Slime pores conspicuous white spots. A dark brown colour around pale gill apertures. Ventral finfold dark brown and caudal fin reddish brown (
<figureCitation box="[238,328,1939,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,849,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-372@3.[151,1435,849,1725]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. (A) Holotype (B) Gill apertures (GA) Eptatretus wadgensis sp. nov., CMFRI DNR.: GC.1.1.1.1, 400mm in TL, fresh specimen (photo: K.R. Aju)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809924/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Specimens dark brown when preserved in formalin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,998,1975,2002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1615,2038]" box="[199,998,1975,2002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1975,2001]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">Distribution</emphasis>
